pageContent.subText: The cell incubator will bring founders together to launch the first 10 cells through ixo.world. This will demonstrate how cyber-cellular organisations operate. Each cell will have an impact mission and implement at least one project, with accountable targets. Up to 100 applications will be accepted for the first cohort. The top 10 candidates will be invited to join the incubator. The work of this incubator will be considered done only after at least 8 of the teams have achieved their cell recruitment and project performance targets. On successful completion, cells will be rewarded with an economic stake in the ixo.world relayer node, valued at 5,000 Euro.
pageContent.subTitle: Mission
pageContent.text: The Cell Incubator connects a network of teams who are founding their own cells to implement pilot projects through ixo.world. A cyber-cell is a highly networked, intelligent form of organisation. This enables people to achieve a shared mission through self-coordination, self-governance, sharing common resources and having access to the same sources of truth. Cells mimic how nature operates in ways that are decentralised, self-regulating and adaptive. The human immune system is a great example. This organisational model is popular with high-performing teams. Now we can virtualise and augment cellular orgranisations with cybernetic capabilites, so that they can sense and respond much more rapidly and precisely to changes in the world. Members of the incubator cell will support each other to learn about, develop and implement cybernetic tools for their use-cases, using artificial intelligence, blockchain smart contracts, p2p communications, electronic rights and decentralised finance mechanisms.
pageContent.title: Incubating cells

data.shortDescription: Assisting you to organise with cyber-powers to achieve your mission.
data.title: Cell Incubator

data.longDescription: Cellular organisations (Cells) are a highly effective coordination mechanism for people to self-organise and self-govern towards achieving a common mission. By definition, cells are decentralised, autonomous, locally responsive, adaptable, hyper-networked, intelligent and purpose-driven. They are highly suitable for virtual and remote teams to work together and share common resources. [Learn more](https://github.com/ixofoundation/docs/blob/master/ixo/concepts/cell-nodes/README.md)

media.caption: People form a Cell to pursue a shared mission
media.text: People form a Cell to pursue a shared mission

pageContent.subText: Cell nodes are the digital infrastructure for all types of cellular organisations. These are decentralised, autonomous data stores with digital agency and cryptographic signing capabilities. Cell nodes enable data to be communicated quickly and securely through webs of trust. All participants in a cell have access to the same information and share intelligence both within their own cell node and with other organisations, through Internet of Impact networks.The digital artefacts created by a cell (such as Project Documents) are stored in the node as stateful records which are referenced in a distributed ledger. Public metadata are stored using the Interplanetary File System (IPFS). This allows cell nodes to retain a form of memory that can be stigmergically shared and rapidly amplified when cells need to be replicated or re-activated.

After the avalanche, it took us a week to climb out. Now, I don't know exactly when we turned on each other, but I know that seven of us survived the slide... and only five made it out. Now we took an oath, that I'm breaking now. We said we'd say it was the snow that killed the other two, but it wasn't. Nature is lethal but it doesn't hold a candle to man.

media.caption: Funding the transition to technology-enabled education
media.text: Alpha-bonds are an innovation for funding access to educational technologies

pageContent.subText: The ixo foundation is undertaking a multi-year research program on innovative financing to rapidly scale proven interventions that improve the quality of primary education. This project is part of a series of technology experiments using the ixo protocol and alpha-bonds.
pageContent.subTitle: Research Objective
pageContent.text: India has made enormous progress in education to achieve a 99% rate of primary school access. The Sustainable Development Goals have now focused attention on improving the quality of education to ensure that children in school are actually learning. A typical student in India is at least two grades behind the level expected for their age in literacy and numeracy. The Quality Education India Development Impact Bond (DIB) programme supports Indian education providers to improve learning outcomes for primary school children through an innovative results-based funding mechanism.
pageContent.title: Development Impact Bonds for Education

data.shortDescription: Innovative financing for scaling learning outcomes from quality primary education programmes.
data.title: Quality Primary Education
